  "title": "Field Service Engineer/Senior Field Service Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities</p><p>1. Equipment Installation, Calibration, and Acceptance</p><p>- Perform installation and functional verification of back-end semiconductor equipment (such as Die Attach, Thermal Compression, AOI, TC Bonder, etc.) at customer sites.</p><p>- Carry out machine calibration, production line integration, and SAT/FAT acceptance testing in accordance with SOPs and customer requirements.</p><p></p><p>2. Technical Support and Troubleshooting</p><p>- Handle equipment signal abnormalities, software/hardware failures, and fixture-related issues in real time.</p><p>- Conduct Root Cause Analysis (RCA), propose corrective actions, and report findings to the engineering team at headquarters.</p><p>- Provide on-site and remote technical support to ensure equipment uptime meets customer expectations.</p><p></p><p>3. Equipment Maintenance and Servicing</p><p>- Perform scheduled Preventive Maintenance (PM) and equipment performance calibration.</p><p>- Maintain and update maintenance logs, service reports, and parts replacement records.</p><p>- Evaluate equipment health conditions and recommend optimization or improvement actions.</p><p>4. Customer Training and Technical Documentation</p><p>- Train customer engineers and operators on equipment operation, maintenance, and safety procedures.</p><p>- Prepare service reports, technical documentation, and troubleshooting guides.</p><p>- Support the development and update of internal knowledge base materials.</p><p>5. Internal Collaboration and Cross-Country Technical Communication</p><p>- Collaborate with engineering, quality, and R&D teams at the Korea headquarters.</p><p>- Provide feedback on equipment functions, software performance, and design improvement needs.</p><p>- Support new product testing, demos, and customer pilot-run activities.<br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Candidate must possess at least a Diploma, Bachelor’s Degree, or Master’s Degree in Electrical, Mechanical, Automation, Optics, or other relevant engineering disciplines.</p></li><li><p>Minimum of 3 years of hands-on working experience in machine setup, installation, maintenance, and packaging equipment.</p></li><li><p>Strong communication skills with a careful, detail-oriented, and methodical working attitude.</p></li><li><p>Patient, responsible, and able to work well both independently and as part of a team.</p></li></ul>",
